100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On September 22, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing global disarmament and the ongoing tensions in Europe. In the United States, the trial of John Scopes, a teacher accused of violating Tennessee's Butler Act by teaching evolution, continued to attract nationwide attention. Meanwhile, in Turkey, the government announced reforms aimed at modernizing the nation, reflecting its ongoing shift towards secularism under Mustafa Kemal Atatürk.
